  "body": "Peer-to-peer in referenced in the honest validator spec, talking about subscribing to topics and broadcasting.\r\n\r\nThe implementations talk about libp2p, which rather than a specific peer-to-peer protocol, seems to be actually a family of different protocols for discovering, connection, broadcasting, etc. i.e. a library of different protocols.\r\n\r\nWhile I didn't find a .NET Core version of libp2p, I did find what seems to be an equivalent library with a collection of different P2P protocols, https://github.com/richardschneider/peer-talk\r\n\r\nBoth libp2p and peer-talk appear to implement the protocols used for IPFS, so if Eth2 is using the same protocols we may be able to use that.\r\n",
